body:
**Description**

Filling a polygon from a SKPath fills the entire canvas, not just the interior of the path. This only happens when you fill the line using MoveTo/LineTo. 

Maybe it is because of the InverseWinding and IsConcave...

**Code**

```

public void FillPath(SKCanvas g, SKPath gp)
        {

            SKPoint[] points =  new SKPoint[]{
            new SKPoint(728.4489f,48.174187f),
            new SKPoint(618.8237f,168.18684f),
            new SKPoint(573.079f,375.3296f),
            new SKPoint(662.4753f,478.39078f),
            new SKPoint(842.29297f,508.02264f),
            new SKPoint(940.2133f,237.2352f),
            new SKPoint(728.4489f,48.174187f)
            };
            gp = new SKPath();

            for (int i = 0; i < points.Length - 1; i++)
            {
                gp.MoveTo(points[i]);
                gp.LineTo(points[i + 1]);
            }

            gp.FillType = SKPathFillType.InverseWinding;

            using (var p = new SKPaint() { Color = SKColors.Green, Style = SKPaintStyle.Fill })
            {
                g.DrawPath(gp, p); 
            }
        }
```

**Expected Behavior**

Expect only the interior of the SKPath to be filled.

**Actual Behavior**
Drawing with Fill
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7605046/203147746-4a4fa040-af52-453a-bc51-36513b453d76.png)

Drawing only the stroke (ie, commenting out ```g.DrawPath(gp, p);```
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7605046/203147833-fbf690df-e25f-4b48-8651-6e3803367fd3.png)


**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  SkiaSharp 2.88.3
- Last known good version:  Unknown
- IDE:  VS 17.4.1
- Platform Target Frameworks: So far I am only able to test on Windows using Maui/Net7
